<task id="040" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-B-07 `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` schema-aware — array-typed fields render as bulleted list (fixes R5 TL;DR bug)</title>
    <phase>Phase B — Schema-Aware Output</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>4-5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>032, 033</dependencies>
    <blocks>041, 042, 048</blocks>
    <tags>frontend, react, fluent-ui</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Frontend code implementation in `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx`; modifies a shared workspace widget consumed across SpaarkeAi surfaces; fixes a R5-surfaced rendering bug (Gap C); 6+ steps; FULL rigor mandatory per CLAUDE.md §8 (code-review + adr-check at Step 9.5).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>B-G3</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Touches `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` which task 041 ALSO modifies. Task 040 lands FIRST (array rendering); task 041 lands SECOND (object rendering). They cannot run truly in parallel — set 041 dependency to 040.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Update `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` to be schema-aware: at render time, READ
    the action's `outputSchema` (populated by tasks 032 + 033) and dispatch on field
    type. THIS TASK ships ARRAY-TYPED field rendering: when `outputSchema` declares a
    field as `array` of `string` (e.g., `tldr: string[]` from
    `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`), accumulate streaming token deltas until
    `streaming_complete`, JSON.parse the accumulated chunk, and render the resulting
    array as a Fluent v9 bulleted list. This structurally fixes the R5 SC-18 bug where
    `tldr` rendered as raw streaming JSON tokens (Gap C in R5 lessons-learned).

    Object-typed field rendering is task 041 (sibling; same file; lands AFTER this). The
    two tasks share the same file but they share the core "accumulate tokens until
    streaming_complete → JSON.parse → dispatch by type" plumbing — task 040 establishes
    the plumbing + array case; task 041 extends the dispatch with the object case.

    The widget MUST: (a) gracefully fall back to today's string rendering when
    `outputSchema` is absent (backward compatibility for actions not yet migrated); (b)
    handle malformed JSON in accumulated chunks (parse failure → emit error state, log,
    do NOT crash); (c) respect Fluent UI v9 theming + dark mode (ADR-021); (d) keep the
    streaming-display "in-progress" indicator until `streaming_complete` fires.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    SPAARKE platform developer. Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with deep
    familiarity with the SpaarkeAi widget framework, the `StructuredOutputStreamWidget`,
    the streaming chat completion delta protocol, and the existing widget registry. Comfortable
    with ADR-012 (shared components) + ADR-021 (Fluent v9 dark-mode compliance) +
    ADR-030 (PaneEventBus 4-channel closed).
  </role>

  <goal>
    `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` is updated to read the action's `outputSchema`
    prop at mount time, accumulate streaming token deltas internally, dispatch on
    schema-declared field type when `streaming_complete` fires, and render fields typed
    `array: string` as a Fluent v9 bulleted list (`<ul><li>...</li></ul>` styled with
    `tokens` from `@fluentui/react-components`). The fix is verified by SC-18-style
    end-to-end test (invoke `summarize-document-for-workspace@v1`; observe `tldr` field
    renders as bullets — NOT raw streaming JSON tokens). Backward compatibility: actions
    without `outputSchema` continue to render as strings (current behavior). All unit
    tests pass; UI tests pass; dark-mode compliance verified per ADR-021.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="widget">src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx</file>
    <file purpose="component-model">docs/architecture/SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md</file>
    <file purpose="component-skill">.claude/skills/fluent-v9-component/SKILL.md</file>
    <file purpose="r5-lessons">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared components — `StructuredOutputStreamWidget` lives in `@spaarke/ai-widgets` (or equivalent shared library); changes here propagate to all consumers. Use Fluent UI v9 components + tokens; do NOT introduce v8 or custom-CSS color values.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 dark-mode compliance — every color, background, and border MUST use Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens (`tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`, etc.); NO hard-coded hex values; NO white-in-dark / black-in-light. Dark-mode UI test mandatory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-030">PaneEventBus — no new channels; widget MAY emit additive event types on existing channels but this task does not require any new events.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-05">PaneEventBus 4-channel preserved; no 5th channel.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec NFR-11">Backward compatibility — actions without `outputSchema` MUST render as today (string formatting). Fallback path is the legacy behavior.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec FR-28">Array-typed field rendering: accumulate token deltas; JSON.parse on `streaming_complete`; render as bulleted list. Fixes R5 TL;DR bug.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Verify BFF publish-size; report delta vs prior baseline; ≤+5 MB R6 total budget per NFR-02. Frontend code changes typically do NOT affect BFF publish size; confirm in task notes (expect 0 MB delta on BFF side; frontend bundle delta acceptable if &lt;+50 KB).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Malformed JSON in accumulated chunk MUST be handled gracefully — emit error state to UI, log error to telemetry, do NOT crash the widget or other tabs.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Widget MUST keep the streaming-display "in-progress" indicator until `streaming_complete` fires; do NOT prematurely flip to rendered state.</constraint>
  </constraints>

