    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 token-styled bulleted list" location=".claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md">
        Use `makeStyles` or `tokens.colorNeutralForeground1`/`tokens.spacingHorizontalM`
        from `@fluentui/react-components`. Styled-`ul` with consistent vertical rhythm
        matches the workspace tab visual language.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Streaming token-delta accumulation" location="src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx">
        Inspect existing widget for the current streaming protocol — likely a `useEffect`
        subscribed to PaneEventBus delta events. Accumulate in component state as raw
        string until a `streaming_complete` marker arrives; then JSON.parse; then
        dispatch.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="R5 lessons-learned Gap C" location="projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/lessons-learned.md">
        Schema-aware rendering implicit — fixed structurally by this task. The widget
        rendered streaming JSON token deltas as if they were the final string. Solution:
        accumulate-then-parse-then-dispatch.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      R5 SC-18 walkthrough surfaced that `tldr: string[]` rendered in the workspace tab
      as raw JSON fragments ("[\"first bullet point\", \"se...") because the
      widget treated the streaming delta as a string token to display, not as a
      JSON-array-being-streamed. The widget had no way to know the field type — that
      knowledge lives on the action's `outputSchema`. With tasks 030, 032, and 033
      shipping the action-side schema declaration, this task plumbs the widget to
      consume it.

      Fix design: at mount, read `outputSchema` from props (or from a workspace-tab
      hydration call). Accumulate token deltas in component state as raw string.
      When `streaming_complete` arrives, JSON.parse the accumulated value (with
      try/catch). Inspect the schema's `properties` map. For each top-level field
      typed `{ type: "array", items: { type: "string" } }`, render the value as a
      Fluent v9 bulleted `<ul>`. Object-typed dispatch comes in task 041.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx (MODIFIED — main implementation file)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/workspace/StructuredOutputStreamWidget.test.tsx (NEW or MODIFIED — unit tests covering schema-aware array dispatch + fallback path)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/notes/task-040-widget-implementation-evidence.md (NEW)</file>
    </relevant-files>
    <related-work>
      <item>Task 041 EXTENDS this widget with object-typed field rendering — depends on 040 first.</item>
      <item>Task 042 CapabilityRouter dedup depends on this widget being the canonical render path (eliminates duplicate-fire).</item>
      <item>Task 048 Phase B integration test exercises this widget end-to-end.</item>
      <item>Tasks 032 + 033 supply the data foundation (action `outputSchema` populated).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + RIGOR LEVEL">
      Check context. Declare:

      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: FULL
      📋 REASON: Frontend code implementation in shared widget; fixes R5 Gap C rendering
                 bug; 6+ steps; ADR-012 + ADR-021 binding (Fluent v9 + dark-mode)
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS: all 12 steps below INCLUDING Step 9.5 quality gates + ui-tests
                         (Step 9.7)
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>
    <step order="1" name="Review Progress">
      Read TASK-INDEX.md; confirm 040 status 🔲; deps (032, 033) complete. Verify the
      action `outputSchema` data is populated on Spaarke Dev (smoke query).
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Gather Resources">
      Read inputs + knowledge. Read the existing
      `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx` IN FULL. Read SPAARKEAI-COMPONENT-MODEL.md and
      SPAARKEAI-WORKSPACE-ARCHITECTURE.md for the widget contract surface. Read R5
      lessons-learned Gap C.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Design Schema-Aware Plumbing">
      Sketch: how does the widget receive `outputSchema`? Options: (a) prop drilled from
      tab manager; (b) hydration call to BFF at mount; (c) workspace state model
      (Pillar 6a — not yet shipped in Phase B). Choose (a) prop-drilled for Phase B —
      simpler, no Phase C dependency. Tab manager passes `outputSchema` when installing
      the widget. Document the decision.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Implement Accumulate-Parse-Dispatch Plumbing">
      In `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.tsx`: add `outputSchema?: JsonSchema` prop. Add
      `accumulatedText: string` state. On each streaming delta event, append to state.
      On `streaming_complete`: try-parse accumulated text; on success, hold the parsed
      object in state; on failure, set error state + log.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Implement Array Dispatch (THIS TASK)">
      For each top-level field in the parsed object: lookup field type from
      `outputSchema.properties[fieldName].type`. If `array` of `string`: render
      `<ul>{value.map(v =&gt; &lt;li&gt;{v}&lt;/li&gt;)}</ul>` styled with Fluent v9 tokens
      (`makeStyles({ list: { marginInlineStart: tokens.spacingHorizontalM, color:
      tokens.colorNeutralForeground1, ... } })`). Use `<li>` semantics; do NOT use bullet
      Unicode characters. Object dispatch is OUT of scope for this task (lands task 041);
      for now object-typed fields use the legacy string-rendering fallback.
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Implement Backward-Compatible Fallback">
      If `outputSchema` prop is absent OR JSON parse fails: render accumulated text as a
      string (current behavior). This preserves existing actions that haven't been
      migrated.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Author Unit Tests">
      Add `StructuredOutputStreamWidget.test.tsx` cases:
      (a) schema-aware: array-typed `tldr` renders as `<ul>` with N `<li>` elements;
      (b) backward-compat: no `outputSchema` → renders as string (legacy);
      (c) malformed JSON: error state rendered, no crash;
      (d) streaming-in-progress indicator until `streaming_complete`;
      (e) ADR-021: no hard-coded colors (snapshot inspect `makeStyles` tokens used).
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Build + Verify BFF Publish-Size">
      Run `npm run build` for the widget library. Confirm build succeeds. Confirm BFF
      publish-size delta is 0 MB (frontend change does NOT affect BFF binary; verify per
      CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 4: `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o
      deploy/api-publish/`). Report delta vs prior baseline.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify Acceptance Criteria">
      Walk through every &lt;acceptance-criterion&gt; below. Record evidence.
    </step>
    <step order="9.5" name="Quality Gates (FULL rigor)">
      Run `code-review` against the widget + test changes. Run `adr-check`; verify
      ADR-012 (shared components / Fluent v9), ADR-021 (dark-mode tokens), ADR-029
      (publish-size delta = 0 BFF-side), ADR-030 (PaneEventBus channels unchanged).
      Both gates MUST pass.
    </step>
    <step order="9.7" name="UI Tests (per ui-tests section)">
      Run UI tests defined below via ui-test skill (Chrome integration). Verify rendered
      output + dark-mode compliance.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Document + Complete">
      Update TASK-INDEX.md: 040 🔲 → ✅. Reset `current-task.md`. Report completion.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="npm">Build the widget library; run unit tests</tool>
    <tool name="dotnet">Build + publish BFF for publish-size verification</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit on R6 worktree branch</tool>
    <tool name="ui-test">Run UI tests via Chrome integration</tool>
