    <criterion testable="true">Object-typed fields fall back to legacy string rendering in this task (task 041 ships the object dispatch).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Backward compatibility: actions without `outputSchema` render as today (string formatting) with NO regression on non-migrated actions.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Malformed JSON in accumulated chunk is handled — error state emitted to UI; widget does NOT crash; error logged to telemetry.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Streaming "in-progress" indicator persists until `streaming_complete` fires.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR-021 dark-mode compliance: zero hard-coded colors; all colors use Fluent UI v9 semantic tokens (verified by code review + dark-mode UI test).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">ADR-030 PaneEventBus: no new channels added (verified by inspection); widget consumes existing `workspace.*` channel events only.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Unit tests cover: array dispatch happy path; backward-compat fallback; malformed JSON; streaming indicator. All pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (frontend change does not affect BFF binary; confirmed in task notes).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">UI tests (4 defined above) pass via ui-test skill; SC-18 scenario verified end-to-end.</criterion>
